<Layout title="Licenses - Sojorn" description="Sojorn licensing model and open source acknowledgments">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2 text-egyptianBlue">Licenses</h1>
    <p class="mb-8 text-sm text-gray-500">Last Updated: February 21, 2026</p>

    <div class="prose prose-blue max-w-none text-gray-700">

      <!-- ─── SOJORN LICENSING ─── -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Sojorn Licensing</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Sojorn uses a split licensing model. Each component is licensed independently:</p>

      <table class="w-full mb-6 text-sm border-collapse">
        <thead><tr class="border-b bg-gray-50"><th class="text-left py-3 px-4">Component</th><th class="text-left py-3 px-4">License</th><th class="text-left py-3 px-4">Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b"><td class="py-3 px-4 font-medium">Go API Engine</td><td class="py-3 px-4"><a href="https://mariadb.com/bsl11/" class="text-egyptianBlue underline" target="_blank">BSL 1.1</a></td><td class="py-3 px-4">Core platform engine. Non-production use permitted. Converts to Apache 2.0 on 2030-02-21.</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b"><td class="py-3 px-4 font-medium">AI Gateway</td><td class="py-3 px-4"><a href="https://mariadb.com/bsl11/" class="text-egyptianBlue underline" target="_blank">BSL 1.1</a></td><td class="py-3 px-4">AI moderation pipeline. Same terms as the API engine.</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b"><td class="py-3 px-4 font-medium">Flutter App</td><td class="py-3 px-4"><a href="https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0" class="text-egyptianBlue underline" target="_blank">Apache 2.0</a></td><td class="py-3 px-4">Mobile and desktop client. Free to use, modify, and distribute.</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b"><td class="py-3 px-4 font-medium">Admin Panel</td><td class="py-3 px-4"><a href="https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.html" class="text-egyptianBlue underline" target="_blank">AGPL-3.0</a></td><td class="py-3 px-4">Administration interface. Must share modifications if deployed as a network service.</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b"><td class="py-3 px-4 font-medium">Website</td><td class="py-3 px-4"><a href="https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.html" class="text-egyptianBlue underline" target="_blank">AGPL-3.0</a></td><td class="py-3 px-4">Public website (sojorn.net). Same terms as admin panel.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <p class="mb-4">All source code is publicly available at <a href="https://gitlab.com/patrickbritton3/sojorn" class="text-egyptianBlue underline" target="_blank">gitlab.com/patrickbritton3/sojorn</a>.</p>
      <p class="mb-6">For commercial licensing of BSL-licensed components: <a href="mailto:hello@sojorn.net" class="text-egyptianBlue underline">hello@sojorn.net</a></p>

      <!-- ─── WHAT IS THE BSL? ─── -->
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3 text-egyptianBlue">What is the Business Source License?</h3>
        <p class="mb-2">The BSL 1.1 is a source-available license created by <a href="https://mariadb.com/bsl11/" class="text-egyptianBlue underline" target="_blank">MariaDB</a>. It allows you to read, copy, modify, and redistribute the code, and use it for non-production purposes (development, testing, education, research). Production use requires a commercial license.</p>
        <p class="mb-2">The key feature of the BSL is the <strong>Change Date</strong>: four years after each release, the code automatically converts to a permissive open source license (Apache 2.0 in our case). This means all Sojorn API code will eventually be fully open source.</p>
        <p>Companies like <a href="https://www.cockroachlabs.com/" class="text-egyptianBlue underline" target="_blank">CockroachDB</a>, <a href="https://surrealdb.com/" class="text-egyptianBlue underline" target="_blank">SurrealDB</a>, and <a href="https://mariadb.com/" class="text-egyptianBlue underline" target="_blank">MariaDB</a> use the BSL to balance open development with sustainable business models.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- ─── OPEN SOURCE ACKNOWLEDGMENTS ─── -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4">Open Source Acknowledgments</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">Sojorn is built on the work of hundreds of open source projects. We are grateful to every contributor. Below is a listing of the major dependencies we use, organized by component.</p>

