      <!-- License Notes -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">License Notes</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 space-y-2">
        <li><strong>ffmpeg_kit_flutter_new</strong> uses <strong>LGPL-3.0</strong>. This is the most restrictive dependency in the Flutter app. LGPL requires that users can replace the LGPL'd library. Since it is dynamically linked, this requirement is satisfied.</li>
        <li><strong>PM2</strong> uses <strong>AGPL-3.0</strong>, but it runs as a standalone process manager on the server and is not linked into Sojorn code. No copyleft obligation flows to Sojorn.</li>
        <li><strong>LLaMA Guard 3</strong> uses Meta's <strong>Llama 3 Community License</strong>, which is free for commercial use for services with fewer than 700 million monthly active users.</li>
        <li>The <strong>PostgreSQL License</strong> is a permissive BSD-style license specific to the PostgreSQL project.</li>
        <li>The <strong>SIL Open Font License (OFL-1.1)</strong> allows free use, modification, and redistribution of fonts.</li>
        <li>All other dependencies use <strong>MIT</strong>, <strong>BSD-2-Clause</strong>, <strong>BSD-3-Clause</strong>, <strong>Apache-2.0</strong>, or <strong>ISC</strong> licenses &mdash; all permissive licenses with no copyleft requirements.</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="mb-4 text-sm text-gray-500">This page lists direct dependencies only. Each dependency may have its own transitive dependencies with their own licenses. The Flutter app resolves approximately 195 packages total; the Go backend resolves approximately 100 modules total. For complete dependency trees, see <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded">sojorn_app/pubspec.lock</code> and <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded">go-backend/go.sum</code> in our <a href="https://gitlab.com/patrickbritton3/sojorn" class="text-egyptianBlue underline" target="_blank">source repository</a>.</p>
